      "span_text": "According to Landis's criteria for consistency and reliability, the strength of agreement was considered poor when the correlation coefficient was below 0.00, slight when it was between 0.00 and 0.20, fair when it was between 0.21 and 0.40, moderate when it was between 0.41 and 0.60, substantial when it was between 0.61 and 0.80, and almost perfect when it was above 0.81 [CITATION_1] ."
